Copper rose for the first session in
four days in  London  after Chinese Premier  Wen Jiabao  underlined
that  China  is willing to invest in  Europe ’s bond market,
potentially easing the region’s debt crisis and improving the
outlook for metals demand. The euro gained.  Market News:  Metals News: 